**who —** Marie Curie — a FEMALE · generations sphere — one age, one woman

**what —** The physicist and chemist who pioneered the study of radioactivity, discovered polonium and radium, and remains the only person to win Nobel Prizes in two different sciences.

**where —** 1867–1934 · Poland / France — the top woman of her age, restored to the record  Framework inputs: the generations of women; the record restored  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The physicist and chemist who pioneered the study of radioactivity, discovered polonium and radium, and remains the only person to win Nobel Prizes in two different sciences.

**how —** Crystallized from the documented life and work of Marie Curie.

**◌ the mythos —** The physicist and chemist who pioneered the study of radioactivity, discovered polonium and radium, and remains the only person to win Nobel Prizes in two different sciences. the foremost woman of her generation, written back into the lineage

